16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aAs the number of people affected by dementia continues to rise, this is the first in-depth examination of related services dedicated to the unique demands of remote and rural settings. Contributors from the UK, Australia, North America and Europe explore the experiences and requirements of those living with dementia and those caring for them in personal and professional capacities in challenging geographical locations. For practitioners, researchers, academics and policy makers, this book is an essential review of evidence and strategies to date, and a guide to future research needs and opportunities for improvements in rural dementia practice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aHEALTH & FITNESS / Diseases / Alzheimer's & Dementia.2bisacsh1 aAuer, Stefanie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBauer, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBlackberry, Irene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChiovitte, Jessica M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavis, Hilary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFarmer, Jane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFarmer, Jane, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGrant, Sharon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHicks, Ben, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHyde, Andy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHöfler, Margit, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aInnes, Anthea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aInnes, Anthea, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/voca